gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Mavericks 115, Timberwolves 108
gameRecap.excerpt: The Mavericks defeated the Timberwolves, 115-108. Kyrie Irving (35 points, eight rebounds, five assists, six 3PM) and Luka Doncic (34 points, six rebounds, eight assists, five 3PM) combined for 69 points for the Mavericks in the victory, while Anthony Edwards tallied 36 points and 10 rebounds for the Timberwolves in the losing effort. The Mavericks win their third consecutive games as they improve to 22-15 on the season, while the Timberwolves fall to 25-10.
